      "review_summary": "The PR changes `packages/terminal-core/src/note.ts` so OpenClaw passes pre-wrapped note text to Clack through a widened virtual output stream.\n\nPR surface: Source +5. Total +5 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. for source-level reproduction: session-lock doctor output reaches the shared `note()` helper, and pinned Clack 1.4.0 hard-wraps final note content using `getColumns(output) - 6`. I did not run a live `openclaw doctor` scenario in this read-only review.",
